1
00:00:00,109 --> 00:00:06,560
On the bright side, companionship with people with big ideas raises the level of our thinking.

2
00:00:06,829 --> 00:00:10,879
Close contact with ambitious people gives us ambition.

3
00:00:11,389 --> 00:00:18,560
Experts agree that the person you are today, your personality, ambitions, present status in life,

4
00:00:18,590 --> 00:00:22,000
are largely the result of your psychological environment.

5
00:00:22,269 --> 00:00:27,840
And experts agree also that the person you will be 1, 5, 10,

6
00:00:27,840 --> 00:00:33,280
20 years from now, depends almost entirely on your future environment.

7
00:00:33,869 --> 00:00:37,599
You will change over the months and years, this we know.

8
00:00:37,789 --> 00:00:44,080
But how you will change depends on your future environment, the mind food you feed yourself.

9
00:00:44,269 --> 00:00:51,280
Let's look now at what we can do to make our future environment pay off in satisfaction and prosperity.

10
00:00:53,229 --> 00:00:56,160
Recondition yourself for success.

11
00:00:56,910 --> 00:01:04,559
The number one obstacle on the road to high-level success is the feeling that major accomplishment is beyond reach.

12
00:01:05,069 --> 00:01:12,239
This attitude stems from many, many suppressive forces that direct our thinking toward mediocre levels.

13
00:01:12,910 --> 00:01:18,080
To understand these suppressive forces, let's go back to the time we were children.

14
00:01:18,429 --> 00:01:21,520
As children, all of us set high goals.

15
00:01:21,629 --> 00:01:27,280
At a surprisingly young age, we made plans to conquer the unknown, to be leaders,

16
00:01:27,470 --> 00:01:34,560
to attain positions of high importance, to do exciting and stimulating things, to become wealthy and famous.

17
00:01:34,830 --> 00:01:38,239
In short, to be first, biggest, and best.

18
00:01:38,590 --> 00:01:43,760
And in our blessed ignorance, we saw our way clear to accomplish these goals.

19
00:01:44,030 --> 00:01:45,200
But what happened?

20
00:01:45,390 --> 00:01:50,320
Long before we reached the age when we could begin to work toward our great objectives,

21
00:01:50,429 --> 00:01:53,919
a multitude of suppressive influences went to work.

22
00:01:54,349 --> 00:02:00,799
From all sides we heard, it's foolish to be a dreamer, and that our ideas were impractical,

23
00:02:00,830 --> 00:02:06,320
stupid, naive, or foolish, that you have got to have money to go places,

24
00:02:06,510 --> 00:02:11,520
that luck determines who gets ahead, or you've got to have important friends,

25
00:02:11,710 --> 00:02:14,400
or you're too old or too young.

26
00:02:14,989 --> 00:02:21,679
As a result of being bombarded with the you-can't-get-ahead-so-don't-bother-to-try propaganda,

27
00:02:21,869 --> 00:02:25,679
most people you know can be classified into three groups.
